                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.38/56.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-30T11:00:00-04:49">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1915—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Commission with full powers, in accordance with your November 12, appointed:
                    Solon Ménos, Haitian Minister at Washington, President; Auguste Magloire,
                    administrator of finance, Port au Prince, and Pierre Hudicourt, lawyer and
                    plenipotentiary to second peace conference at the Hague, members. Commission
                    expects to leave this week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
